Duda, who has scored five goals this season, plays as an attacking midfielder and sometimes as a secondary striker but he can also play deeper and has an eye for a pass.

Legia only signed him last summer on a free after he allowed his contract to run down at previous club Kosice.

The Poles value Duda in the £7m bracket but Everton would be looking to pay around £3.5m if they press ahead.

Everton do not wish to sell their players but are wary of increased interest in James McCarthy - on whom Arsenal and Tottenham are keen - and Ross Barkley. 

